## 🧠 What I Learnt – Detailed Personal Reflections from Doing the Work

- The difference between theory and practice is enormous. Reading about SQL injection is one thing; actually crafting the payload that bypasses login and uploads a shell made me feel the real danger.
- Remediation is harder and more important than exploitation. Fixing issues without breaking legitimate functionality taught me patience and attention to detail.
- Writing the report while everything was fresh made the documentation far more accurate and useful.
- Mapping every action to Essential Eight turned abstract controls into concrete, lived experience.
- I now have real stories (“I exploited vsftpd in under 30 seconds, then hardened it so the attack is impossible”) that I can confidently discuss in any ADF interview or selection board.

This single practical session has dramatically increased my confidence and competence.

